{
  "texts": [
    "This layer connects each neuron of the preceding layer to each neuron of the current layer.",
    "The previous layer's output is flattened and delivered to a fully connected layer that linearly modifies the data before sending it to a nonlinear activation function [128].",
    "CNN architecturesVarious CNN architectures carry out classification tasks, including ResNet, VGG Net, Inception, Xception, DenseNet, EfficientNet, MobilenetV2, and many more.",
    "On the other hand, segmentation tasks are carried out by U-Net, V-Net, FCN, SegNet, DRUNET, and many different architectures [129].",
    "With the aid of CNN, the number of parameters can be significantly reduced, overfitting can be prevented, and the information gleaned from an image may be preserved."
  ]
}